| >!TFTPBoot
| © Pace Micro Technology plc, 1999

| Disable the Break and Escape keys, and switch NumLock off
Fx 229 1
Fx 247 170
Fx 202 4 251
Fx 118

| Clear the screen, move the text cursor down a little and switch it off
Echo |L|M|M|M|M<23><1><0><0><0><0><0><0><0><0>

| Store the location of the mount where the run-time Baseline is
Set NetRoot$Dir  NFS::NFSBoot.$
|Set NetRoot$Dir  LanManFS::ARMBoot.$
Set NetRoot$Path <NetRoot$Dir>.

| Store the location of the root of this boot sequence
Set STBRoot$Dir  Resources:$.STB
Set STBRoot$Path <STBRoot$Dir>.

| This path is needed until we have established what is local and what is on the mount
Set Root$Path <STBRoot$Path>,<NetRoot$Path>

| Mount the appropriate server-hosted Baseline directory
NFS:Mount -host 136.170.32.3 NFSBoot /stbboot/live/TFTP
|LanManFS:Mount -host 136.170.32.4 ARMBoot ARMBoot

| Download the Baseline archive
TFTPLoadModule 136.170.129.41 Arc400,ffa

| Set up some important system variables for booting
Set STBSplash$Disable "True"
Set Alias$@RunType_FEB Obey -c %*0

| Ensure we have enough free memory for utilities like Repeat
WimpSlot -next 256K
Run Root:!STBBoot.Utilities.FreePool

| Start the global STB booting application
Run Root:!STBBoot
